## 🔍 What is RAG?

**RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation)** is an AI architecture pattern that enhances a Large Language Model (LLM) by giving it the ability to **search and retrieve** relevant information from your own documents before generating an answer.

> In simple terms: RAG teaches an AI to **look things up** before it **speaks**.

A standard LLM only knows what it learned during training. RAG breaks that limitation by adding a **dynamic retrieval step** — the AI can now reference any document you give it, updated at any time, without retraining.

```
Standard LLM:    Question ──────────────────────────► LLM ──► Answer
                                                     (uses only training knowledge)

RAG:             Question ──► Search Documents ──► LLM ──► Answer
                                                     (uses YOUR documents + training)
```

---

## ❓ Why RAG Exists

Large Language Models face three core limitations:

| Limitation | Problem | RAG Solution |
|-----------|---------|-------------|
| **Knowledge Cutoff** | Training data has a fixed date — anything after that is unknown | Upload fresh documents anytime |
| **Hallucination** | LLMs sometimes confidently make up incorrect facts | Answers are grounded in real retrieved text |
| **No Private Data Access** | LLMs cannot access your internal files, databases, or PDFs | RAG lets you plug in private documents |

RAG was introduced in a 2020 paper by Meta AI researchers and has since become the **most widely used pattern** for building production AI applications on top of LLMs.

