## 💡 Real-Life Analogy

Think of RAG like a **student taking an open-book exam**:

```
Without RAG (Closed-book exam):
  The student answers from memory only.
  Risk of wrong answers, gaps in knowledge.

With RAG (Open-book exam):
  The student searches the textbook for the relevant section,
  reads it, then writes the answer.
  More accurate. Grounded in real content.
```

Or even simpler:

```
   Google Search        +        ChatGPT
  (finds information)     (explains information)
             ↓
            RAG
     (finds AND explains)
```

