## 📐 Chunking Strategies

Different chunking strategies suit different document types:

```
┌────────────────────────┬─────────────────────────┬──────────────────────┐
│  Strategy              │  How It Works            │  Best For            │
├────────────────────────┼─────────────────────────┼──────────────────────┤
│  Fixed-size            │  Split every N tokens    │  General purpose     │
│  (most common)         │  with overlap            │  plain text          │
├────────────────────────┼─────────────────────────┼──────────────────────┤
│  Sentence-based        │  Split at sentence       │  Articles, reports   │
│                        │  boundaries (.)          │  prose documents     │
├────────────────────────┼─────────────────────────┼──────────────────────┤
│  Recursive character   │  Try paragraph →         │  Mixed-format docs   │
│                        │  sentence → word         │  (LangChain default) │
├────────────────────────┼─────────────────────────┼──────────────────────┤
│  Semantic              │  Group by topic meaning  │  Complex, dense docs │
│                        │  using embeddings        │                      │
├────────────────────────┼─────────────────────────┼──────────────────────┤
│  Document-specific     │  By headers / sections   │  Markdown, HTML,     │
│  (structural)          │  (H1, H2, H3 etc.)       │  structured manuals  │
└────────────────────────┴─────────────────────────┴──────────────────────┘
```

**Overlap explained:**

```
Chunk size = 100 tokens, Overlap = 20 tokens

  Chunk 1:  [Token 1  ──────────────────── Token 100]
  Chunk 2:            [Token 81 ──────────────────────── Token 180]
                       ▲──── 20 token overlap ────▲
  Chunk 3:                          [Token 161 ─────────── Token 260]

Overlap ensures context is not lost at chunk boundaries.
```

