## 🔬 Advanced RAG Techniques

Beyond basic RAG, several advanced techniques improve accuracy:

### 1. Hybrid Search

```
  Question
     │
     ├──► Semantic Search (vector similarity)  ─┐
     │                                           ├──► Merge Results ──► LLM
     └──► Keyword Search (BM25/TF-IDF)        ─┘

Combines meaning-based AND keyword-based search for better recall.
```

### 2. Re-ranking

```
  Top-20 chunks from vector search
              │
              ▼
     Re-ranking Model
     (cross-encoder)
              │
              ▼
  Top-3 most relevant chunks  ──► LLM
```

After initial retrieval, a second, more precise model re-ranks the candidates to send only the best chunks to the LLM.

### 3. Query Rewriting

```
  User: "what did we decide last sprint about auth?"
              │
              ▼
     Query Rewriter (LLM)
              │
              ▼
  Rewritten: "authentication decisions sprint planning meeting"
              │
              ▼
     Better retrieval results
```

### 4. Parent-Child Chunking

```
  Store small chunks for precise search.
  But retrieve parent (larger context) for answering.

  Parent:  Full section (512 tokens) ──► sent to LLM
  Child:   Sentence (64 tokens)      ──► used for matching
```

