## 📎 Quick Reference

| Term | Definition |
|------|-----------|
| **Embedding** | Numerical vector representation of text meaning |
| **Vector DB** | Database optimized for similarity search over vectors |
| **Chunk** | A small segment of a document, typically 256–512 tokens |
| **Cosine Similarity** | Metric to measure how close two vectors are (0–1 scale) |
| **Top-K** | Retrieve the K most similar chunks (typically 3–5) |
| **Context Window** | Maximum tokens an LLM can process at once |
| **Hallucination** | When an LLM confidently states something false |
| **Grounding** | Anchoring AI answers in real retrieved source text |
| **LlamaIndex** | Python framework for building RAG pipelines |
| **LangChain** | Python framework for chaining LLM + retrieval workflows |

